472
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:56,073
<i>That you stole from the skies</i>

473
00:42:56,880 --> 00:43:05,310
<i>It's that old devil moon</i>
<i>In your eyes</i>

474
00:43:05,840 --> 00:43:11,870
<i>You and your glance make this romance</i>
<i>Too hot to handle</i>

475
00:43:12,200 --> 00:43:18,548
<i>Stars in the night blazin' their light</i>
<i>Can't hold a candle</i>

476
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:20,950
<i>To your razzle-dazzle</i>

477
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:25,955
<i>You got me flyin' high and wide</i>

478
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:31,629
<i>On a magic carpet ride</i>

479
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:37,953
<i>Full of butterflies inside</i>

480
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:40,276
<i>I wanna cry</i>

481
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:43,078
<i>I wanna croon</i>

482
00:43:44,120 --> 00:43:47,556
<i>I want to laugh like a loon</i>

483
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:53,356
<i>It's that old devil moon</i>

484
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:56,433
<i>In your eyes</i>

485
00:43:58,560 --> 00:44:02,348
<i>Just when I think I'm</i>

486
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:07,118
<i>Free as a dove</i>

487
00:44:07,560 --> 00:44:12,475
<i>Old devil moon</i>
<i>Deep in your eyes</i>

488
00:44:12,880 --> 00:44:15,519
<i>Blinds me with...</i>

489
00:44:16,800 --> 00:44:19,234
<i>-...love</i>
<i>-Yeah</i>

490
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:53,869
-Howard, old buddy!
-Hey, Woody!

491
00:45:04,240 --> 00:45:06,196
How's the Luther Burbank
of the swamp?

492
00:45:06,400 --> 00:45:07,958
-Mr. Moneybags.
-How you doing?

493
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:10,310
l've been waiting for you.
Where you been?

494
00:45:12,360 --> 00:45:14,590
Sharon, meet Howard.
Howard, this is Sharon.

495
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:16,836
How do you do? Nice to meet you.

496
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:20,198
Woody, l'm glad you're here.
l got the list all made out.

497
00:45:20,400 --> 00:45:26,077
Fifty feet of styrene tubing, quarter inch,
250 pounds of nitrogen tripalminate--

498
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:29,829
The voice you hear is the voice
of the greatest research botanist today.

499
00:45:30,040 --> 00:45:32,395
He's gonna change
our whole way of life...

500
00:45:32,600 --> 00:45:35,637
...and he's gonna do it
with these little flowers right here.

501
00:45:35,840 --> 00:45:38,274
-They're all his babies.
-We're doing it together.

502
00:45:38,640 --> 00:45:40,915
Woody thought it up,
and l'm growing them up.

503
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:43,759
l ain't nothing but
a suede-shoe boy peddling tobacco.

504
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:46,428
But Howard--
Howard is the first man in history...

505
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:50,519
...to mate the mint plant with tobacco.
You realize what that means.

506
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:51,869
No.

507
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:56,110
You are looking at
the mentholated tobacco plant.

508
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:59,235
Here, smell.

509
00:45:59,640 --> 00:46:02,757
Smell the mint-julep nicotine.

510
00:46:05,480 --> 00:46:08,199
That's nice. Really smells lovely.

511
00:46:08,440 --> 00:46:12,035
lt's a whole new form of tobacco life.

512
00:46:12,400 --> 00:46:16,029
-lt only has one drawback.
-What's that?

513
00:46:16,520 --> 00:46:18,590
Well, it doesn't burn.

514
00:46:19,320 --> 00:46:20,753
lt doesn't burn?

515
00:46:20,960 --> 00:46:22,632
lt's worse than asbestos.

516
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:25,229
lt actually puts fires out.
We're working on it.

517
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:26,589
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

518
00:46:26,800 --> 00:46:31,157
Now that you're all back,
fat with cash...

519
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:34,798
...gotta get to work.
Once l rig the styrene tubing...

520
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:37,798
...l'll take the nitrogen tripalminate
in powdered form--

521
00:46:38,000 --> 00:46:40,514
That's what l've been meaning
to talk to you about.

522
00:46:40,720 --> 00:46:45,077
What's that? The styrene tubing or the
nitrogen tripalminate in powdered form?

523
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:48,511
-The cash.
-Yeah, what about the cash?

524
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:52,429
l got some great things going. l made
some contacts you wouldn't believe.

525
00:46:52,640 --> 00:46:55,393
Wait, wait. Contacts? No cash?

526
00:46:57,520 --> 00:46:58,999
Not a dime.

527
00:47:11,120 --> 00:47:14,556
Well, you didn't bring back any cash,
l'll go out and get some.

528
00:47:15,120 --> 00:47:16,553
How?

529
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:19,710
l'll get a job. Yeah.

530
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:25,677
But you've got a job, Howard.
That's to make it burn. Make it burn!

531
00:47:33,040 --> 00:47:34,996
ls that dedication?

532
00:47:36,240 --> 00:47:37,389
Mr. Mahoney?

533
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:41,719
You're going to make plenty
of money for everyone?

534
00:47:41,920 --> 00:47:43,194
You bet.

535
00:47:43,400 --> 00:47:45,755
Without doing a stitch of work for it?

536
00:47:46,040 --> 00:47:47,234
Why not?

537
00:47:47,600 --> 00:47:50,831
And is that what you call
the''Mahoney theory of economics''?

538
00:47:51,720 --> 00:47:54,029
No, but that's a pretty good name for it.

539
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:58,919
Why don't you grow ordinary tobacco
that does burn?

540
00:47:59,120 --> 00:48:00,997
Never get rich that way.

541
00:48:01,640 --> 00:48:04,108
See you soon, Sharon.
Hey, Howard, buddy!

542
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:02,758
Don't take that personal. He's trained
to do that to anyone what ain't white.

543
00:49:09,760 --> 00:49:13,230
-You're the new boy from the agency.
-Yeah.

544
00:49:13,440 --> 00:49:15,431
Okay, Stonewall.

545
00:49:17,040 --> 00:49:19,235
Ain't l seen you somewhere?

546
00:49:22,080 --> 00:49:25,117
-You worked here as a butler, didn't you?
-Oh, no, no.

547
00:49:25,400 --> 00:49:27,994
No, sir.

548
00:49:28,800 --> 00:49:31,394
Well, you'll like working here, boy.

549
00:49:31,640 --> 00:49:35,155
l've hired all of the senator's butlers
for the past 10 years.

550
00:49:35,360 --> 00:49:39,751
Hundreds of them. Of course,
he's a little intolerant at times...

551
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:42,235
...but that's his blood pressure.

552
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:45,470
-What's your name?
-Howard.

553
00:49:46,160 --> 00:49:48,355
Let me see you serve that julep.

554
00:49:53,520 --> 00:49:58,196
Rawkins won't like that. That's no way
to serve a julep. lt's too fast.

555
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,755
Get some shuffle into it.

556
00:50:01,160 --> 00:50:04,357
You've seen some of the new movies,
like <i>Birth of a Nation</i>...

557
00:50:04,560 --> 00:50:06,790
...and <i>Gone With the Wind</i>, haven't you?

558
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:09,670
-Here, George, like this.
-Howard.

559
00:50:09,880 --> 00:50:11,871
Yeah, okay, Jackson.

560
00:50:15,960 --> 00:50:20,954
Your julep, sir. Master Rawkins, sir.

561
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:23,958
All frosted and minty....

562
00:50:29,240 --> 00:50:30,958
You see, George?

563
00:50:38,080 --> 00:50:40,355
Why do l have to shuffle?

564
00:50:40,560 --> 00:50:43,870
Now, l don't have to explain that to you.

565
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:50,235
lt makes for kindly feelings
between employer and employee.

566
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:55,112
Once more, now. Try it again.
And not so fast this time.

567
00:51:02,360 --> 00:51:04,032
How did you do that again?

568
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:06,197
l don't understand you, Jackson.

569
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:09,119
l mean, you don't walk or talk
like you're supposed to.

570
00:51:09,320 --> 00:51:12,278
You don't know how to serve a julep
like you're supposed to.

571
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:13,959
You educated or something?

572
00:51:15,320 --> 00:51:17,515
l'm working on my master's.

573
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:20,468
Working on your master's what?

574
00:51:21,400 --> 00:51:23,152
lt's a college degree.

575
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:28,512
Now, don't mention the word''college''
around the senator. lt upsets him.

576
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:32,156
But that's beside the point.
Do you want a job here, or don't you?

577
00:51:34,280 --> 00:51:37,238
Yes, sir, l do.

578
00:51:37,680 --> 00:51:38,749
l needs the money.

579
00:51:38,960 --> 00:51:41,872
Well, that's all the more reason
for you to make good here.

580
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:46,631
Then when you get your college degree,
why, you got a job here for life.

581
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:48,836
-Buzz!
-Oh, l'll speak to you later.

582
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:51,349
You go around back
and keep practicing, hear?

583
00:51:51,560 --> 00:51:54,154
-Buzz, where are you?
-l'm over here, senator.

584
00:51:54,400 --> 00:51:57,870
-l can't seem to see you.
-lt's these columns, senator.

585
00:51:58,080 --> 00:52:00,355
-They sort of get in the way.
-Nonsense.

586
00:52:00,560 --> 00:52:03,711
Those columns haven't
moved an inch in a hundred years.

587
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:05,399
Meet me down by the glider.

588
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:18,039
Yep. Fine job you done yesterday, Buzz...

589
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:22,233
-...buying up all that land.
-Yes, sir. Bought up the whole valley.

590
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:24,431
Except one little parcel.

591
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:29,430
That'll teach them bureaucrats to stay
where they belong, in Washington.

592
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:32,355
Cheap electric power.

593
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:35,558
Why don't they build their dam
on the Potomac...

594
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:38,433
...instead of desecrating
this heaven-given valley...

595
00:52:38,640 --> 00:52:40,392
...with a lot of copper wire.

596
00:52:41,200 --> 00:52:46,593
Electrocuting innocent bullfinches
and sparrows.

597
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,559
Gentlemen...

598
00:53:07,680 --> 00:53:11,309
...the festering tides of radicalism
are upon us.

599
00:53:12,880 --> 00:53:16,156
But before l yield up
our glorious South...

600
00:53:16,360 --> 00:53:19,238
...and her sister commonwealth,
the U.S. of A...

601
00:53:20,040 --> 00:53:22,031
...l will lay down my life.

602
00:53:22,920 --> 00:53:27,152
l will do more than that. l will filibuster.

603
00:53:28,480 --> 00:53:32,837
Back, you crackpots. Forward, America.

604
00:53:33,640 --> 00:53:37,269
Forward to the hallowed principles
of our forefathers.

605
00:53:37,880 --> 00:53:43,034
Forward to the sweet tranquility
of the status quo.

606
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:47,548
Forward to yesterday.

607
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:04,916
Get this dog off-- Get him off me.

608
00:54:05,120 --> 00:54:08,078
Caught him dead to rights, senator.
Spank on your property.

609
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:11,875
Oh, damn it, sheriff, can't you arrest
a couple of chicken thieves...

610
00:54:12,080 --> 00:54:14,275
...without disturbing
the whole countryside?

611
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:18,519
Worse than chicken thieves this time.
These are geologists from Washington.

612
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:20,677
Geologists?

613
00:54:25,680 --> 00:54:27,079
Two?

614
00:54:28,240 --> 00:54:30,993
-l only see one.
-Senator.

615
00:54:31,320 --> 00:54:35,393
This is a geological survey of the soil
in this area in connection with the dam.

616
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:38,319
l don't need nobody to tell me
what's on my land.

617
00:54:38,520 --> 00:54:40,351
Especially one of his kind.

618
00:54:40,560 --> 00:54:42,994
Look, l read the findings on this meter.

619
00:54:43,200 --> 00:54:45,873
lt detected gold on your property
this afternoon.

620
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:51,910
You found what on my property?

621
00:54:52,120 --> 00:54:54,395
lt located an amazing
concentration of gold.

622
00:54:54,600 --> 00:54:57,160
The meter reacted so violently,
it broke the needle.

623
00:54:57,360 --> 00:55:00,636
We're sorry about that needle,
but we'll reimburse you. Now....

624
00:55:00,840 --> 00:55:04,879
Just where did this unfortunate
needle-breaking accident occur?

625
00:55:05,200 --> 00:55:08,192
Parcel lot number seven,
right outside Rainbow Valley.

626
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:11,710
-Oh, my God.
-What are you mumbling about, Buzz?

627
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:14,275
lnvite these gentlemen
up on the veranda.

628
00:55:14,480 --> 00:55:17,074
lt isn't every day we're honored
with the presence...

629
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:20,113
...of two distinguished scientists
from Washington, D.C.

630
00:55:20,320 --> 00:55:22,754
Sorry, senator,
we've got more ground to cover.

631
00:55:22,960 --> 00:55:25,190
Gentlemen, l wish you'd accept
my hospitality.

632
00:55:25,400 --> 00:55:26,913
Senator?

633
00:55:29,200 --> 00:55:31,077
That was the strip l told you about.

634
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:34,272
-What strip?
-The one we couldn't buy.

635
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:39,678
Well, gentlemen, l'm sorry
you gotta rush off like this...

636
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:42,075
...but you hurry back
real soon, now, hear?

637
00:55:43,160 --> 00:55:45,151
We couldn't buy it? Who bought it?

638
00:55:45,360 --> 00:55:47,920
We found out it was a man
named Finian McLonergan.

639
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:50,395
Yankee brain!
Why weren't you prepared for him?

640
00:55:50,600 --> 00:55:52,955
l never saw him before.
He's an immigrant.

641
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:55,594
My family's been having trouble
with immigrants...

642
00:55:55,800 --> 00:55:59,315
-...ever since they come to this country!
-Don't you get excited!

643
00:55:59,520 --> 00:56:01,397
You'll feel better when
you've had your julep.

644
00:56:01,600 --> 00:56:04,910
To hell with my julep!
Get me a Bromo, quick.

645
00:56:05,640 --> 00:56:07,278
Howard!

646
00:56:08,040 --> 00:56:12,192
Howard! Bring the senator
a Bromo-Seltzer, quick!

647
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:15,995
And call my lawyer.
Tell him to find a loophole.

648
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:18,395
Where's that Bromo?

649
00:56:18,840 --> 00:56:23,231
-Where's that Bromo, Howard?
-My loophole's choking me.

650
00:56:24,040 --> 00:56:25,792
Where's that Bromo?

651
00:56:26,280 --> 00:56:29,750
Coming, master. Coming.

652
00:56:29,960 --> 00:56:34,795
l'm coming all in there, yes, sir.
Yeah, l'm coming.

653
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:38,390
Will you hurry up on that Bromo?!

654
00:56:38,600 --> 00:56:40,591
You're gonna enjoy it
once l get to you.

655
00:56:40,800 --> 00:56:44,509
-Get him his Bromo!
-Coming in there fast as l can.

656
00:56:44,720 --> 00:56:49,589
-Will you hurry up with it?!
-Coming right there, fix your head good.

657
00:56:49,800 --> 00:56:53,429
Mercy, sure gonna make you
feel like you flying.

658
00:56:53,640 --> 00:56:57,474
-Please, please hurry up with the--
-Come on, Howard!

659
00:56:57,680 --> 00:56:59,318
Come on!

660
00:57:00,520 --> 00:57:02,875
Howard, come on!

661
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:06,073
-Please bring me my--
-Howard!

662
00:57:06,360 --> 00:57:08,954
Oh, Lord, l'm coming in.

663
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:11,993
Howard! Come on, bring that!
Get over here!

664
00:57:19,920 --> 00:57:23,037
<i>How are things in Glocca Morra?</i>

665
00:57:23,320 --> 00:57:26,835
<i>Is that willow tree</i>
<i>Still weepin' there?</i>

666
00:57:27,840 --> 00:57:31,310
<i>Does that laddie</i>
<i>With the twinklin' eye</i>

667
00:57:32,840 --> 00:57:34,831
<i>Come whistlin' by</i>

668
00:57:35,320 --> 00:57:37,550
<i>And does he walk away</i>

669
00:57:37,920 --> 00:57:39,956
<i>Sad and dreamy there</i>

670
00:57:40,440 --> 00:57:42,556
-Sharon!
-Aye?

671
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:45,991
-Haven't you laundered my shirt yet?
-lt's coming, it's coming.

672
00:57:46,400 --> 00:57:48,470
<i>Not to see me there?</i>

673
00:57:56,640 --> 00:57:59,552
Not so hard. You'll be wringing
the lrish out of the linen.

674
00:57:59,760 --> 00:58:01,876
lt is the neck of the Mahoney
l'm wringing.

675
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:05,834
Oh, good, good, good. Lover's quarrel.
Healthy sign.

676
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:07,712
Are you sure?

677
00:58:08,080 --> 00:58:10,958
l know true devotion when l see it.

678
00:58:11,160 --> 00:58:14,948
l know a fine, upstanding darling
of a man when l see one.

679
00:58:15,280 --> 00:58:17,430
He's leaving for parts unknown
this morning.

680
00:58:17,640 --> 00:58:19,358
He's what? He's running out on you?

681
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:22,757
He's off to sell tobacco
that doesn't burn. He's a schemer.

682
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,394
-You're well rid of him.
-An impractical dreamer.

683
00:58:25,600 --> 00:58:28,319
-lt's deplorable.
-Total no-good bounder.

684
00:58:28,520 --> 00:58:30,715
Get the wretch out of your mind.

685
00:58:31,520 --> 00:58:34,637
-He's just like you.
-Aye, a darling of a man.

686
00:58:34,840 --> 00:58:38,674
Now, look. Now, just a minute.
Now, don't you be crying.

687
00:58:45,120 --> 00:58:47,509
A special rose...

688
00:58:48,280 --> 00:58:50,191
...for your hair.

689
00:58:50,760 --> 00:58:53,149
lt has magical properties.

690
00:58:53,680 --> 00:58:56,148
Beautiful bride you'll be.

691
00:58:58,120 --> 00:59:00,588
All by myself, or is there a man involved?

692
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:02,552
Aye, there is.

