lt's all my fault.

1560
02:02:59,400 --> 02:03:01,595
Oh, the merciful saints forgive me.

1561
02:03:02,880 --> 02:03:07,237
Her broken father will forgive you too,
if you'd just spare a little magic for her.

1562
02:03:07,440 --> 02:03:09,829
<i>Oh, anything, Mr. McLonergan.</i>
<i>I'd do anything!</i>

1563
02:03:10,040 --> 02:03:12,634
<i>Turn the senator white again</i>
<i>and save Sharon's life!</i>

1564
02:03:12,840 --> 02:03:14,558
<i>Og, we've only 20 minutes!</i>

1565
02:03:14,760 --> 02:03:16,671
Well, Sambo.

1566
02:03:17,200 --> 02:03:19,668
You don't look like
you lightened up a smidgen.

1567
02:03:19,880 --> 02:03:22,030
l could do it in a minute
and have 19 left.

1568
02:03:22,240 --> 02:03:24,310
Thank heavens.
l knew you wouldn't fail me.

1569
02:03:24,520 --> 02:03:26,636
Why not wait 19 minutes...

1570
02:03:26,840 --> 02:03:30,037
...and leave it all to the last minute.
lt's more dramatic.

1571
02:03:30,240 --> 02:03:31,468
Now, Og, now!

1572
02:03:31,680 --> 02:03:34,717
-lt's a matter of life and death!
-Very well, Mr. McLonergan.

1573
02:03:34,920 --> 02:03:37,150
-l just need one thing from you.
-What is it?

1574
02:03:37,360 --> 02:03:40,158
-Speak up, man. What do you need?
-A crock of gold.

1575
02:03:40,600 --> 02:03:44,036
Give me strength to resist me
own strength to keep from choking him!

1576
02:03:44,240 --> 02:03:46,708
You stand there and pretend
you haven't got it?

1577
02:03:46,920 --> 02:03:49,559
-But l haven't got it!
-Then why can't l find it?

1578
02:03:49,760 --> 02:03:53,753
l dug more holes this weary night
than all the gophers in Christendom!

1579
02:03:53,960 --> 02:03:56,599
Think back to when you buried it.
What were you doing?

1580
02:03:56,800 --> 02:03:59,030
l don't know! How would l know? l....

1581
02:03:59,240 --> 02:04:02,789
l had a jug of whiskey in one hand
and the crock of gold in the other--

1582
02:04:03,000 --> 02:04:05,673
You might've buried the jug
and swallowed the crock.

1583
02:04:05,880 --> 02:04:09,555
You Machiavellian, half-pint pirate,
stealing me property! l want it back.

1584
02:04:09,760 --> 02:04:12,479
-Please, Mr. McLonergan, l wish l had it.
-Where is it?

1585
02:04:12,680 --> 02:04:16,150
-l haven't got it.
-l'll throttle it out of you! l want it back!

1586
02:04:16,640 --> 02:04:18,756
Where is it? Where is it?

1587
02:04:20,280 --> 02:04:22,111
You perfidious little wretch....

1588
02:04:22,320 --> 02:04:25,756
-l'll throttle it out of you.
-l don't know where it is!

1589
02:04:26,400 --> 02:04:27,515
Where is it?

1590
02:04:27,720 --> 02:04:29,233
l wish l....

1591
02:04:29,560 --> 02:04:31,915
-Where is it?
-l wish l....

1592
02:04:38,280 --> 02:04:40,271
lt's almost dawn.

1593
02:04:46,840 --> 02:04:48,353
<i>They can't do it to her.</i>

1594
02:04:48,560 --> 02:04:51,199
It'll be one of me or 100 of them!

1595
02:04:55,040 --> 02:04:56,359
Og...

1596
02:04:56,560 --> 02:05:00,838
...if you have a mite of merciful magic
left, help me save me daughter's life.

1597
02:05:01,040 --> 02:05:02,234
Will you, now?

1598
02:05:05,960 --> 02:05:08,918
Oh, Susan, it's a crisis.

1599
02:05:09,560 --> 02:05:11,232
A crisis.

1600
02:05:13,360 --> 02:05:16,113
They're gonna burn Sharon
for a witch.

1601
02:05:16,560 --> 02:05:18,437
She's not a witch.

1602
02:05:19,400 --> 02:05:23,154
She must've been standing by the crock
when she made the wish.

1603
02:05:23,360 --> 02:05:24,793
Susan...

1604
02:05:25,000 --> 02:05:26,274
...you must've been there.

1605
02:05:26,480 --> 02:05:28,710
Where was Sharon standing?

1606
02:05:29,720 --> 02:05:31,119
Where was she...?

1607
02:05:31,320 --> 02:05:33,754
Oh, it's no good asking you.
You can't hear me.

1608
02:05:33,960 --> 02:05:36,110
l'll have to ask somebody else.

1609
02:05:37,000 --> 02:05:38,479
There's no time.

1610
02:05:38,680 --> 02:05:40,079
Susan, come here.

1611
02:05:40,280 --> 02:05:41,759
Sit down. Look...

1612
02:05:41,960 --> 02:05:45,589
...l'll dance you the questions,
and you dance me the answers, you see?

1613
02:05:45,800 --> 02:05:47,870
Questions, answers, right?

1614
02:05:57,320 --> 02:05:59,231
l'll put it another way.

1615
02:06:41,320 --> 02:06:43,834
Susan, Susan, Susan....

1616
02:06:44,960 --> 02:06:46,393
You're a darling girl...

1617
02:06:46,600 --> 02:06:48,795
...and l love you very much...

1618
02:06:49,480 --> 02:06:52,313
...but l just wish to God you could talk.

1619
02:06:53,960 --> 02:06:55,109
l love you.

1620
02:06:59,040 --> 02:07:01,190
l love you.

1621
02:07:03,880 --> 02:07:05,916
Beautiful new words.

1622
02:07:07,360 --> 02:07:08,509
Will you say them again?

1623
02:07:08,720 --> 02:07:10,278
l love you.

1624
02:07:10,480 --> 02:07:11,833
She loves me.

1625
02:07:12,200 --> 02:07:13,838
She loves me!

1626
02:07:14,120 --> 02:07:16,953
You're talking, Susan!
Where was Sharon standing?

1627
02:07:17,160 --> 02:07:19,993
-l love you!
-Oh, l know that.

1628
02:07:20,720 --> 02:07:22,631
But you're talking.

1629
02:07:23,000 --> 02:07:26,151
That means l must've wished you into it.

1630
02:07:27,240 --> 02:07:30,391
Which means l must've been standing
over the crock.

1631
02:07:30,720 --> 02:07:33,712
The crock, the crock....

1632
02:07:34,120 --> 02:07:37,669
lt looks like you are
permanently a black man.

1633
02:07:51,760 --> 02:07:53,273
Oh, my heavens.

1634
02:07:53,480 --> 02:07:54,754
What have l done?

1635
02:08:02,960 --> 02:08:04,632
The crock.

1636
02:08:09,640 --> 02:08:11,631
There's only one wish left.

1637
02:08:12,360 --> 02:08:13,918
The last one.

1638
02:08:16,240 --> 02:08:18,913
lf l use it to wish the senator white...

1639
02:08:21,280 --> 02:08:23,032
...l'd never be a leprechaun again.

1640
02:08:26,720 --> 02:08:29,393
-We gotta sound the alarm.
-Yes.

1641
02:08:29,600 --> 02:08:32,194
Mr. Rodgers, sound the alarm.

1642
02:08:33,400 --> 02:08:34,674
Fire.

1643
02:08:35,400 --> 02:08:36,958
Fire.

1644
02:08:37,880 --> 02:08:38,835
Fire.

1645
02:08:39,040 --> 02:08:41,235
But l don't wanna be mortal.

1646
02:08:42,160 --> 02:08:44,628
l wanna go back to fairyland.

1647
02:09:00,000 --> 02:09:01,877
Fairyland was never like this.

1648
02:09:05,280 --> 02:09:06,235
Where is she?

1649
02:09:07,760 --> 02:09:11,355
Rawkins, you blackguard,
l wish you white!

1650
02:09:18,880 --> 02:09:20,996
-She turned him white.
-He's done it!

1651
02:09:23,120 --> 02:09:24,269
Thank you, Og.

1652
02:09:24,480 --> 02:09:26,072
Release those prisoners!

1653
02:10:28,280 --> 02:10:30,475
Come on! Keep that water
coming in here!

1654
02:10:30,680 --> 02:10:32,955
-Keep the water coming!
-Keep the water coming.

1655
02:10:33,160 --> 02:10:35,993
-Keep the water coming!
-Keep the water coming!

1656
02:10:36,200 --> 02:10:38,794
-Keep the water coming!
-Susan is talking!

1657
02:10:39,000 --> 02:10:41,150
-Susan's talking!
-Susan's talking!

1658
02:10:41,360 --> 02:10:44,158
-Susan's talking.
-Susan's talking.

1659
02:10:44,360 --> 02:10:46,749
-Susan's talking.
-Susan's talking.

1660
02:10:46,960 --> 02:10:48,188
Susan....

1661
02:10:48,400 --> 02:10:50,152
Susan's talking?

1662
02:10:50,360 --> 02:10:51,839
Woody!

1663
02:10:52,520 --> 02:10:54,317
-Susan's talking!
-What?

1664
02:10:54,520 --> 02:10:58,069
-Susan's talking!
-ls it true?

1665
02:10:59,240 --> 02:11:02,073
Well, say something, will you?
l've been waiting 20 years!

1666
02:11:02,280 --> 02:11:04,350
lsn't it grandish, Woody?

1667
02:11:07,400 --> 02:11:09,789
You used the crock to wish back
Susan's tongue.

1668
02:11:10,000 --> 02:11:13,276
-Aye.
-And you used up the last wish.

1669
02:11:13,480 --> 02:11:15,914
And now the crock has turned
to worthless dross.

1670
02:11:16,120 --> 02:11:21,513
Aye. Right, Mr. McLonergan.
Dross, worthless dross.

1671
02:11:22,640 --> 02:11:25,200
Hey, Woody! Over here!
The lab's going!

1672
02:11:40,720 --> 02:11:44,793
Four years of sweat and work,
and it's all going up in smoke.

1673
02:11:45,000 --> 02:11:47,036
lt's all right, Howard. We'll put it out.

1674
02:11:49,400 --> 02:11:52,710
No! No! lt's smoking!

1675
02:12:05,280 --> 02:12:08,352
Homegrown mentholated smoke!

1676
02:12:28,720 --> 02:12:33,271
<i>I searched all the earth</i>
<i>And I scanned all the skies</i>

1677
02:12:33,480 --> 02:12:40,909
<i>And I found it at last</i>
<i>In my own true love's eyes</i>

1678
02:12:41,120 --> 02:12:45,352
<i>Look, look</i>
<i>Look to the rainbow</i>

1679
02:12:45,640 --> 02:12:50,714
<i>Follow it over the hill and stream</i>

1680
02:12:50,920 --> 02:12:55,357
<i>Look, look</i>
<i>Look to the rainbow</i>

