02:13:09,000 --> 02:13:15,519
<i>Follow the fellow</i>
<i>Who follows a dream</i>

1685
02:13:21,720 --> 02:13:23,517
l now pronounce you...

1686
02:13:23,720 --> 02:13:25,438
...man and wife.

1687
02:13:59,720 --> 02:14:01,119
Father...

1688
02:14:02,440 --> 02:14:03,589
...are you leaving us?

1689
02:14:06,760 --> 02:14:07,875
Aye.

1690
02:14:08,080 --> 02:14:09,991
l've had Fort Knox.

1691
02:14:10,200 --> 02:14:11,519
l see.

1692
02:14:14,200 --> 02:14:16,111
Things are indeed hopeless.

1693
02:14:16,320 --> 02:14:17,673
Hopeless...

1694
02:14:17,880 --> 02:14:19,632
...but they're not serious.

1695
02:14:19,840 --> 02:14:21,876
But where are you going?

1696
02:14:22,760 --> 02:14:24,591
To find me a rainbow...

1697
02:14:24,800 --> 02:14:26,518
...Finian's Rainbow.

1698
02:14:26,720 --> 02:14:29,632
lt never fails to come up
when a McLonergan is down.

1699
02:14:29,840 --> 02:14:32,798
Sure, there may not be a pot of gold
at the end of it...

1700
02:14:33,000 --> 02:14:35,992
...but there's a beautiful
new world under it.

1701
02:14:38,600 --> 02:14:41,034
Make it shine on Sharon.

1702
02:14:44,880 --> 02:14:46,711
Goodbye, me darling.

1703
02:15:08,160 --> 02:15:11,914
Goodbye, me friends.
l'll see you all in Glocca Morra.

1704
02:15:32,680 --> 02:15:34,830
Sharon, where is Glocca Morra?

1705
02:15:37,680 --> 02:15:39,989
Well, you see,
it's always somewhere...

1706
02:15:40,200 --> 02:15:41,792
...over there.

1707
02:15:42,760 --> 02:15:49,393
<i>So to every weepin' willow</i>

1708
02:15:50,000 --> 02:15:53,993
<i>To each brook along the way</i>

1709
02:15:54,600 --> 02:16:02,473
<i>To each lad who comes a-whistlin'</i>
<i>''Too-ra-lay''</i>

1710
02:16:03,280 --> 02:16:10,436
